The paper deals with image denoising algorithms, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the Sinkhorn-Knopp balancing algorithm, which is related to optimization and iterative procedures, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also introduces a new denoising algorithm, which involves matrix operations and statistical modeling, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
